&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re seeking a Corporate Development Manager to help build and scale IMC&#39;s external engagement function in India. In this role, you will be responsible for managing relationships with exchanges, regulators, brokers, and industry associations, while providing market intelligence that supports IMC&#39;s growth in one of the world&#39;s largest and fastest-evolving capital markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Corporate Development team plays a key role in supporting IMC&#39;s expansion in India, covering all aspects of external engagement, market intelligence, regulatory monitoring, and project management. As part of a small, high-impact team in Mumbai, you will work closely with IMC&#39;s India leadership and trading desks to ensure IMC is well-positioned in the Indian market. The working environment is collaborative, non-hierarchical, and fast-paced. You will manage a wide range of stakeholders both internally and externally, and your initiative, judgment, and ability to build trusted relationships will directly contribute to IMC&#39;s success in India.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong class=&quot;_13fp8yk6c dzswju0&quot;&gt;Your Core Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster and maintain excellent relationships with exchanges, regulators, brokers, custodians, industry associations, and other market participants through regular meetings and proactive engagement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively gather market intelligence relating to regulatory developments, market participants activity, and market structure changes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess implications for IMC of SEBI circulars, exchange notifications, and RBI announcements and coordinate with stakeholders accordingly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the preparation and submission of responses to SEBI consultation papers, ensuring alignment with IMC&#39;s global advocacy positions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the execution of business development and regulatory initiatives, including new market access, exchange product onboarding, and compliance workstreams. Keep key internal stakeholders informed on priorities and status&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend relevant industry conferences and events (FIA, ASIFMA, ANMI, BBF) to build IMC&#39;s network and identify engagement opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Invest in relationships proactively. Be a good partner to counterparts and build IMC&#39;s reputation as a constructive, long-term market participant&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong class=&quot;_13fp8yk6c dzswju0&quot;&gt;Your Skills and Experience:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of experience in Indian financial markets, specifically in one or more of the following: business development at an exchange (NSE, BSE, MCX), institutional/FPI brokerage (exchange relations or operations), or financial markets regulatory consulting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct working experience with NSE and/or BSE in a professional capacity (as an exchange employee or broker exchange relations manager)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong working knowledge of proprietary trading firms and HFT/market-making firms: must already know the relevant issues, have the judgment to assess what is and is not relevant to HFTs, and understand the role of liquidity providers in the market ecosystem&lt;/li&gt;
